  <bioghist id="aspace_7ac8487769855bbd7445c3a172e24c3d">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>David Kalugin was a Mail Handler and later the Suggestions Control Clerk at the United States Post Office's Radio City Station in New York City.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_129218b4cc9abf130d18bd23f19b1c8e">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>This collection consists of materials from two scrapbooks documenting David Kalugin's work at the United States Post Office's Radio City Station in New York, NY. Included are blank and completed forms, correspondence and memoranda, publications, and other printed material relating to Kalugin's work. The folders preserve the original order of the scrapbooks.</p>  </scopecontent>
